               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;Transcription consistent with CEToM notation. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Theres' English Translation:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;table class='table_lines'&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a3&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... Sphaeranthus hirtus to be ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a4&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... destroys the evil ...; this poultice of pap is very salutary || San-&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;dalwood, sacred lotus, vetiver, dill, Hemisdemus indicus, madder, Gym(nema balsamicum),&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a6&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Gymnema lactiferum, sugar, Hygrophila spinosa, agarwood, Tabernaemontana coronaria, to be ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;one (time) the amount, Leucas linifolia, as much as one likes, to be turned into poultices&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... makes white. || Symplocos racemosa, white lotus root, patchouly, &lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b3&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Berberis asiatica, blue lotus, dill, with one (time) the amount of water&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b4&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... to be boiled, are to be turned into poultices with honey ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... of black cherry plum.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 10 has transliteration and notes containing the following translations: &lt;br&gt;
a3 [are to be] made, the face is to be ? , the powder [makes it] white. &lt;br&gt;
a4 destroys pimples, this broth-pill [is] very good. &lt;br&gt;
b1 [of] each [of the preceding] the same [amount], as much kutumbikā as one likes, pills are to be made. &lt;br&gt;
b2 ... makes white: &lt;br&gt;
b3 [of] each the same [amount] in water &lt;br&gt;
b4 is to be cooked with honey [and] pills are to be made. &lt;br&gt;
b5 ... black myrobalan seeds&lt;/p&gt;</item>
